<title>USA: PHH Corp files $3 bln shelf for debt.</title>
<headline>PHH Corp files $3 bln shelf for debt.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>PHH Corp filed a shelf offering with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission on Friday for up to $3 billion in medium-term notes.</p>
<p>Underwriters named in the shelf offering were Credit Suissse First Boston, Goldman Sachs &amp; Co, Merrill Lynch &amp; CO and J.P. Morgan &amp; Co.</p>
<p>The Hunt Valley, Maryland, company said proceeds from the sale will be used to finance assets the company manages for its clients and for general corporate needs.</p>
<p>The company provides vehicle fleet management and leasing services.</p>
